abstract: "A detailed forensic case study documenting a 600+ day sophisticated Android RAT campaign targeting a single victim device (Xiaomi 11T Pro, codename vili). The campaign involved multi-environment attack infrastructure using DSU/GSI installations, Magisk/LSPosed root persistence, baseband diagnostic exploitation via QXDM, device cloning (9 unauthorized clones), and cross-border C2 infrastructure spanning Malaysia and Pakistan. This research documents novel attack techniques, forensic methodology, legal frameworks, and defensive countermeasures."
